task.en: Please help me create a `ContentListView.swift` under the same directory as `ContentView`, and open that file in xcode.

pre_command: osascript -e 'tell application "Xcode" to close windows' && rm -rf /Users/ec2-user/Documents/BenchmarkApp && cp -r /Users/ec2-user/Benchmark_Backup/BenchmarkApp /Users/ec2-user/Documents && cd /Users/ec2-user/Documents/BenchmarkApp && git checkout a68605b && open -a Xcode /Users/ec2-user/Documents/BenchmarkApp
grading_command: osascript -e 'tell application "System Events" to get value of attribute "AXTitle" of window 1 of (first application process whose frontmost is true)' 2>/dev/null | grep -q "BenchmarkApp — ContentListView.swift" && echo "True" || echo "False"
